The paper presents a method for optimising rough set partition sizes using genetic algorithms, which is a machine learning technique falling under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The use of rough set theory and rule extraction also suggests a potential fit for "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Databases" (cs.DB) sub-categories. The analysis of HIV data and prediction accuracy may also fall under "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR) and "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI) sub-categories.
